! This is a sample input of geometry optimization of pseudo octahedral Be6
! cluster.
!
! Bond lengths match with the values in the reference paper (Takagi, H. et al.
! J. Plasma Fuction Res. 2013, 89, 583-598) in two decimal places. Note that
! thresholds (CONV and OPTTOL), code, and calculation of derivative are
! different.
!
! Geometry optimization converged after 25 cycles:
!
!NSERCH:   0  E=       -2.6834632779  GRAD. MAX=  0.0309399  R.M.S.=  0.0116082
!NSERCH:  25  E=       -2.7203930108  GRAD. MAX=  0.0000000  R.M.S.=  0.0000000
!
! In this calculation, initial Hessian is computed with HESS=CALC keyword,
! and this verifies that the initial structure is around transition structure.
! Final optimized structure has no imaginary frequencies.
!
!    1       0.060    A        9.012180    0.000163
!    2       0.028    A        9.012180    0.000171
!    3       0.006    A        9.012180    0.000001
!    4       0.000    A        9.012180    0.000000
!    5       0.021    A        9.012180    0.000026
!    6       0.031    A        9.012180    0.000059
!
! Disclaimer: these parameters are provided so that the correctness of
! the DFTB code in GAMESS can be tested. For production DFTB runs,
! please obtain parameters from the official site www.dftb.org.
!
! You will have to edit the path below in $DFTBSK to run this input.
!
! Do not run DFTB in parallel (except FMO-DFTB, see exam04.inp)!
!
! This file was provided by Yoshio Nishimoto and Stephan Irle, 
! and the parameters were generated by Yoshifumi Nishimura (Nagoya U., Japan).
!
 $CONTRL RUNTYP=OPTIMIZE NPRINT=-5 $END
 $STATPT NSTEP=200 OPTTOL=1.0D-09 HSSEND=.TRUE. HESS=CALC $END
 $SYSTEM MWORDS=40 $END
 $SCF CONV=1.0D-12 $END
 $BASIS GBASIS=DFTB $END
 $DFTB NDFTB=2 $END
!  --- !!!! modify the path below !!!! ---
 $DFTBSK
   Be Be "/usr/local/dftb/parameters/Be-Be.spl"
 $END
